The paper discusses a new learning framework that is able to learn complex algorithms from a few number of examples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions improving language understanding in machines, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions testing the framework on small multi-task datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the model's ability to break down problems into simpler subproblems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
